[assistant] Fixed the failing `mavenVersionForReadsPomPropertiesFromRuntimeClasspath` test.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - `VersionUtil.mavenVersionFor(...)` converts dots in the group ID to path separators.
[assistant] - The runtime JAR has `META-INF/maven/com.fasterxml.jackson.core/...`, but `VersionUtil` looks for `META-INF/maven/com/fasterxml/jackson/core/...`, so it returned `unknownVersion()`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fix:
[assistant] - Added a dedicated test fixture resource at the path `VersionUtil` actually resolves:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/1.12.2/src/test/resources/META-INF/maven/com/example/versionutil/versionutil-fixture/pom.properties`
[assistant] - Updated the test to use that fixture.
[assistant] - Updated native-image resource metadata to include that fixture.
[assistant] 
[assistant] New commit:
[assistant] - `12110225e Fix parquet-jackson VersionUtil maven fixture`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run tests locally, per the original instruction.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Unrelated untracked file remains untouched:
[assistant] - `metadata/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/1.12.2/`
